          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript is used for consultation and reference and is a kind of treatise and manual for the rules and regulations of Hindu law for constructing or laying the foundation of a house (vāstu). Manuscript includes a diagram divided into nine units and each containing the name of a god and a shape, that may be intended for reproduction over the ground during preparation ceremonies, before construction of the house begins (f. i verso-1r)</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Vāstukalpa</title>
              <title type="vernacular">वास्तुकल्प</title>
              <colophon>Colophon: iti vāstukalpaḥ samāptaḥ // saṃvat 1721 varṣe pālgunavadī 11 bhaume likhatam idaṃ pustakaṃ (f. 11v).</colophon>
